    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. The 6 non-assessed factors are acceptable at MRL 2 for a Class II device with medium model influence. Validation results demonstrate NIH prediction error of 11.4% (within 20% criterion) and pump head agreement within 8% across all operating points. The relative hemolysis index RH < 1.0 at all 5 evaluated operating conditions satisfies the acceptance criterion. The credibility evidence is sufficient to support use of the CFD model for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the CPB device.",
